          <h3 class="dest-name">Materuni Waterfall and Coffee Farm Tour</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Immerse yourself in local culture and lush landscapes on the fertile lower slopes of Mount Kilimanjaro. This day trip combines a scenic hike through a green paradise to a stunning 80-meter waterfall with a hands-on, authentic look into the traditional coffee-making process of the Chagga people.</p>
          <details class="trip-details">
            <summary>See itinerary &amp; details</summary>
            <h4>Highlights</h4>
            <ul><li>Hike through pristine tropical valleys to reach the thundering Materuni Waterfall.</li><li>Harvest, grind, and brew your own cup of organic coffee from scratch with local villagers.</li><li>Learn about the rich heritage, traditions, and agricultural lifestyle of the Chagga tribe.</li></ul>
            <h4>Itinerary</h4>
            <ol><li>08:00 AM: Travel from Arusha or Moshi to the historic village of Materuni.</li><li>09:30 AM: Set off on a guided, 40-minute nature walk through local farmlands and lush valleys to the waterfall, where you can swim in the refreshing pool.</li><li>12:30 PM: Head back to the village for a freshly prepared, authentic Chagga hot lunch.</li><li>02:00 PM: Join local farmers in a lively, musical coffee-making session, learning everything from bean to cup.</li><li>04:00 PM: Say goodbye to your hosts and drive back to your accommodation.</li></ol>
            <h4>What is Included</h4><p>Ground transport, local village and waterfall entry fees, professional local guide, traditional hot lunch, and the coffee-making experience.</p>
            <h4>What is Not Included</h4><p>Tipping for village guides, personal gear (waterproof jacket/hiking shoes), and items of a personal nature.</p>
