          <h3 class="dest-name">Arusha Safari</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Perfect for travelers seeking a diverse and active safari experience without spending hours on the road. Located just a short drive from the city center, Arusha National Park packs a staggering variety of ecosystems, from dense montane rainforests to jagged volcanic cones and alkaline lakes, into a compact space.</p>
          <details class="trip-details">
            <summary>See itinerary &amp; details</summary>
            <h4>Highlights</h4>
            <ul><li>Spot striking, rare black-and-white colobus monkeys jumping through the jungle canopy.</li><li>Walk safely alongside herds of zebras and buffaloes accompanied by an armed ranger.</li><li>Take in magnificent, sweeping views of Mount Meru and Mount Kilimanjaro on clear days.</li></ul>
            <h4>Itinerary</h4>
            <ol><li>08:00 AM: Short drive from Arusha town to the park gates.</li><li>09:00 AM: Stretch your legs and walk amongst the wildlife on a unique, close-range foot safari with a national park ranger.</li><li>12:00 PM: Drive out to the glittering Momella Lakes to watch flocks of flamingos, and enjoy a picnic lunch.</li><li>01:30 PM: Tour the edge of the dramatic Ngurdoto Crater (often called &#39;Little Ngorongoro&#39;) to spot herds of giraffes, buffaloes, and warthogs.</li><li>04:30 PM: Depart the park and return to Arusha.</li></ol>
            <h4>What is Included</h4><p>4x4 safari transport, park entrance fees, mandatory armed ranger fee for the walking safari, professional driver-guide, picnic lunch, and mineral water.</p>
            <h4>What is Not Included</h4><p>Canoeing fees (optional add-on), tips, and personal expenses.</p>
