        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Lake Natron</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Ol Doinyo Lengai</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">An intense, off-the-beaten-path expedition to the active stratovolcano revered by the Maasai as the &#39;Mountain of God.&#39; Rising sharply from the arid floor of the Rift Valley near Lake Natron, this challenging day trek is a steep, demanding ascent designed for adventurous climbers seeking raw volcanic geology and surreal landscapes.</p>
          <details class="trip-details">
            <summary>See itinerary &amp; details</summary>
            <h4>Highlights</h4>
            <ul><li>Stand on the slopes of the world&#39;s only active carbonatite volcano.</li><li>Conquer a challenging, steep volcanic ash climb for an ultimate adrenaline rush.</li><li>Gaze out at breathtaking, lunar-like panoramas over the glowing pink waters of Lake Natron.</li></ul>
            <h4>Itinerary</h4>
            <ol><li>Midnight (12:00 AM): Due to intense daytime heat on the barren slopes, the steep climb begins in the cool of the night.</li><li>05:30 AM: Arrive at the summit area in time to witness an unforgettable, dramatic sunrise over the Great Rift Valley.</li><li>07:00 AM: Carefully navigate the steep, loose volcanic ash and gravel paths back down the mountain.</li><li>11:00 AM: Reach the base of the mountain for a well-deserved breakfast/brunch at camp before exploring the shores of Lake Natron.</li><li>02:00 PM: Drive back across the rugged desert tracks to Arusha.</li></ol>
            <h4>What is Included</h4><p>Private 4x4 transport to remote Lake Natron, specialized mountain/Maasai guide fees, village/local authority conservation fees, meals, and emergency first aid support.</p>
            <h4>What is Not Included</h4><p>Technical hiking poles (highly recommended), specialized trekking gear, tips for mountain crew, and personal insurance.</p>
          </details>
