      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="lake-chala">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-chala.jpg" alt="Lake Chala, a volcanic crater lake on the Tanzania and Kenya border" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $118 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Kilimanjaro</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Lake Chala</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Discover a hidden paradise tucked away on the border of Tanzania and Kenya. Lake Chala is a deep, pristine volcanic crater lake fed entirely by clean, underground springs from Mount Kilimanjaro. Surrounded by lush, steep green crater walls, it offers a tranquil oasis perfect for hiking, birdwatching, and peaceful relaxation away from safari crowds.</p>
          <details class="trip-details">
            <summary>See itinerary &amp; details</summary>
            <h4>Highlights</h4>
            <ul><li>Hike down the steep, verdant volcanic crater rim to touch the crystal-clear waters.</li><li>Spot varied birdlife, monkeys, and unique flora in a peaceful, untouched sanctuary.</li><li>Relax or paddle along the quiet edges of a lake split between two countries.</li></ul>
            <h4>Itinerary</h4>
            <ol><li>08:00 AM: Drive from Arusha or Moshi through vibrant rural towns towards the Kenyan border.</li><li>10:00 AM: Arrive at Lake Chala and take a guided walk along the high crater rim to enjoy the panoramic views.</li><li>11:00 AM: Carefully hike down the forest-lined path to the water&#39;s edge.</li><li>12:30 PM: Enjoy a relaxing lunch by the water or at a designated lakeside viewpoint.</li><li>01:30 PM: Spend time exploring the nature trails, birdwatching, or relaxing in the serene environment.</li><li>03:30 PM: Hike back up to the crater rim and drive back to town.</li></ol>
            <h4>What is Included</h4><p>Ground transportation, Lake Chala reserve entry fees, professional local guide, picnic lunch, and bottled water.</p>
            <h4>What is Not Included</h4><p>Kayaking rentals (subject to seasonal availability), tips, and personal items.</p>
