          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Kilimanjaro</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Ndarakwai Ranch</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Explore a pioneering model for community-based conservation on the western slopes of Mount Kilimanjaro. Ndarakwai Ranch is a privately owned, 11,000-acre ranch dedicated to restoring self-sustaining habitats that had been degraded by overgrazing. It offers a unique, intimate wilderness experience where you can see wildlife recovery firsthand.</p>
          <details class="trip-details">
            <summary>See itinerary &amp; details</summary>
            <h4>Highlights</h4>
            <ul><li>Explore an exclusive, private conservation area far away from heavy safari traffic.</li><li>Enjoy guided walking safaris to get close to wildlife on foot safely.</li><li>Support an eco-friendly project that directly benefits local Maasai communities.</li></ul>
            <h4>Itinerary</h4>
            <ol><li>07:30 AM: Depart your hotel and head towards the western Kilimanjaro plains.</li><li>09:30 AM: Meet your resident naturalist and head out on an informative walking safari to spot zebras, elands, giraffes, and wildebeests.</li><li>12:30 PM: Enjoy a fresh, locally sourced hot meal at the Ndarakwai tented camp dining room.</li><li>02:00 PM: Take a short drive to see more remote corners of the ranch or learn about local community anti-poaching initiatives.</li><li>04:00 PM: Head back to Arusha, enjoying views of the plains at dusk.</li></ol>
            <h4>What is Included</h4><p>Private transport, Ndarakwai Ranch conservation fees, services of an experienced resident naturalist, hot lunch, and drinking water.</p>
            <h4>What is Not Included</h4><p>Alcoholic drinks, tips for ranch staff, and items of a personal nature.</p>
          </details>
          <a href="/contact" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">Book This Trip &#x2192;</a>
