      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="chemka-hot-springs">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-chemka.jpg" alt="Kikuletwa Hot Springs turquoise pools surrounded by fig trees" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $85 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Kilimanjaro</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Chemka Hot Springs</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Unwind in an enchanting desert oasis hidden within an arid scrubland plain. Chemka Hot Springs (also known as Kikuletwa) features beautiful pools of warm, crystal-clear turquoise water surrounded by a dense canopy of ancient fig trees and twisting roots. It is the perfect tropical paradise for swimming, relaxing, and refreshing your body after a dusty safari or a grueling mountain trek.</p>
          <details class="trip-details">
            <summary>See itinerary &amp; details</summary>
            <h4>Highlights</h4>
            <ul><li>Swim in perfectly clear, warm geothermal water pools.</li><li>Play around on the rope swings or enjoy a natural &#39;fish pedicure&#39; from tiny river fish.</li><li>Relax in a striking, lush jungle oasis tucked away inside a dry savannah landscape.</li></ul>
            <h4>Itinerary</h4>
            <ol><li>09:00 AM: Depart Arusha or Moshi, driving past sugar cane plantations and baobab patches down bumpy dirt roads.</li><li>10:30 AM: Arrive at the springs; change into swimwear and dive into the inviting, warm turquoise water.</li><li>01:00 PM: Enjoy a freshly cooked hot lunch featuring local favorites like Chipsi Mayai or Nyama Choma.</li><li>02:00 PM: Spend the afternoon lounging on the banks, sunbathing, or enjoying the rope swings.</li><li>04:00 PM: Pack up and drive back to town as the sun begins to set.</li></ol>
            <h4>What is Included</h4><p>Round-trip transport, hot springs entry fees, local guide, freshly prepared local lunch, and bottled water.</p>
            <h4>What is Not Included</h4><p>Swimwear rentals (best to bring your own), alcoholic drinks, and tips.</p>
          </details>
          <a href="/contact" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">Book This Trip &#x2192;</a>
