      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="mount-kilimanjaro-day-hikes">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-dayhike.jpg" alt="Lush montane rainforest trail on Mount Kilimanjaro" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $712 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Kilimanjaro</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Mount Kilimanjaro Day Hikes</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Walk in the footsteps of legends without committing to an arduous week-long trek. This day hike takes you through the historic Marangu Gate and leads you up into the enchanted, mist-shrouded montane rainforest belt of Mount Kilimanjaro National Park, allowing you to experience the magic of the world&#39;s tallest free-standing mountain in a single day.</p>
          <details class="trip-details">
            <summary>See itinerary &amp; details</summary>
            <h4>Highlights</h4>
            <ul><li>Hike through Kilimanjaro’s lush, emerald-green tropical rainforest zone.</li><li>Reach Mandara Huts (2,700 m), the first official base camp on the Marangu Route.</li><li>Peek inside the lush Maundi Crater for panoramic views of the Tanzanian highlands.</li></ul>
            <h4>Itinerary</h4>
            <ol><li>07:30 AM: Drive from Arusha/Moshi through historic Chagga farmlands to the Marangu Gate.</li><li>09:00 AM: Complete park permits and begin hiking through the dense forest canopy, looking for monkeys and bright wild orchids.</li><li>01:00 PM: Reach the camp, explore the clearing, and enjoy a packed lunchbox. Take a short 15-minute side walk to the Maundi Crater viewpoint.</li><li>02:00 PM: Begin your steady walk back down through the forest path.</li><li>04:30 PM: Arrive back at Marangu Gate to receive a completion acknowledgment and meet your driver.</li><li>06:00 PM: Return to your hotel.</li></ol>
            <h4>What is Included</h4><p>Kilimanjaro National Park conservation fees, professional licensed mountain guide fees, private return transfers, picnic lunchbox, and drinking water.</p>
            <h4>What is Not Included</h4><p>Hiking gear (boots, rain coats), tips for your mountain guide, and personal travel insurance.</p>
          </details>
          <a href="/contact" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">Book This Trip &#x2192;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="horseback-riding">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-horseback.jpg" alt="Riders on horseback crossing an open grassland" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $120 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Arusha</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Horseback Riding</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Experience the freedom of the African bush from a completely unique perspective. Located on an exclusive wildlife estate just outside Arusha town, this horseback riding day trip allows you to ride gently alongside plains game, moving quietly through scenery without the noise and disruption of a traditional safari vehicle.</p>
          <details class="trip-details">
            <summary>See itinerary &amp; details</summary>
            <h4>Highlights</h4>
            <ul><li>Ride horses side-by-side with wild zebras, wildebeests, and antelopes.</li><li>Enjoy trails tailored perfectly to your riding level, from beginners to advanced riders.</li><li>Take in a peaceful, eco-friendly outdoor adventure under the shadow of Mount Meru.</li></ul>
            <h4>Itinerary</h4>
            <ol><li>08:00 AM / 02:00 PM: Pick up from your Arusha hotel and transfer to the equestrian center.</li><li>08:45 AM: Meet your riding guide, get fitted for your helmet, and be matched with a horse suited to your experience level.</li><li>09:00 AM: Spend two hours riding across open tracks, viewing wildlife that remains completely relaxed around the horses.</li><li>11:15 AM: Return to the stables for a light snack, coffee, or cold refreshments.</li><li>12:00 PM: Head back to your hotel or onward destination.</li></ol>
            <h4>What is Included</h4><p>Horse rental, professional riding guide, riding safety gear (helmets, chaps), estate entry fees, transfers, and light refreshments.</p>
            <h4>What is Not Included</h4><p>Full meals, personal riding attire (long pants and closed shoes required), and tips.</p>
          </details>
          <a href="/contact" class="dest-cta" style="margin-top:14px;display:inline-flex">Book This Trip &#x2192;</a>
