      <article class="dest-card reveal" id="arusha-shopping-tour">
        <div class="dest-visual"><img src="/images/daytrip-shopping.jpg" alt="Maasai craft market in Arusha, Tanzania" width="800" height="500" loading="lazy"><span class="trip-price">From $70 Per person</span></div>
        <div class="dest-body">
          <div class="dest-tags"><span class="dest-tag">Arusha</span><span class="dest-tag">Day Trip</span></div>
          <h3 class="dest-name">Arusha Shopping Tour</h3>
          <p class="dest-desc">Dive directly into the vibrant colors, scents, and sounds of Arusha, the undisputed safari capital of East Africa. Guided by a trusted local expert, this urban day tour takes you beyond the tourist traps into bustling local markets, artisanal craft co-ops, and fair-trade cultural centers to find authentic Tanzanian treasures.</p>
          <details class="trip-details">
            <summary>See itinerary &amp; details</summary>
            <h4>Highlights</h4>
            <ul><li>Browse through rows of handcrafted beadwork, wood carvings, and colorful Khanga fabrics.</li><li>Visit the vibrant local spice and fruit markets to see daily city life up close.</li><li>Purchase authentic souvenirs safely with a guide who can help you negotiate fair prices.</li></ul>
            <h4>Itinerary</h4>
            <ol><li>09:00 AM: Meet your guide at your hotel and head out to explore the city&#39;s highlights.</li><li>09:30 AM: Walk through the bustling stalls of the Central Market, then browse the vibrant Maasai Craft Market for jewelry and carvings.</li><li>12:00 PM: Drive a short distance to a premier gallery showcasing massive collections of African art, masks, and Tanzanite gemstones.</li><li>01:30 PM: Stop at a cozy local cafe to enjoy traditional Tanzanian coffee and a light lunch.</li><li>03:00 PM: Visit an inspiring workshop where talented, disabled artisans recycle glass and fabrics into beautiful jewelry and homeware.</li><li>04:30 PM: Drop off back at your hotel with your shopping bags.</li></ol>
            <h4>What is Included</h4><p>Services of a dedicated local city guide, private town transport/taxi drops, entry to all artisan cooperatives, and bottled water.</p>
            <h4>What is Not Included</h4><p>Cost of your purchases/souvenirs, lunch/cafe bills, and tips for your guide.</p>
          </details>
